(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

00:36.070 --> 00:38.103
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

01:22.683 --> 01:25.117
(SPEAKS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

01:47.641 --> 01:49.274
(AKBAR SPEAKING
IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

02:48.636 --> 02:50.669
(SHEHZAD SPEAKING
LOCAL LANGUAGE)

03:03.751 --> 03:05.584
(MAN SPEAKS)

03:17.932 --> 03:21.934
Mr. Rahim, it would appear that all
these people have been... abandoned.

03:21.936 --> 03:24.803
First of all,
not a single day goes by

03:24.805 --> 03:27.806
without the Mayor personally
asking me about Orangi Town.

03:28.976 --> 03:31.243
<i>I just got off the phone
with him.</i>

03:31.245 --> 03:34.279
<i>Because of the Mayor
and Special Committee,</i>

03:34.281 --> 03:37.282
<i>this isn't a citywide epidemic.</i>

03:37.284 --> 03:38.517
<i>We do understand.</i>

03:39.820 --> 03:41.887
INTERVIEWER:
Mr. Craig Evans, his wife,

03:41.889 --> 03:45.691
the most high profile survivor
of the first wave.

03:45.693 --> 03:48.460
How would you describe your
wife's condition at this point?

03:48.462 --> 03:50.929
She's stable,
she's out of intensive care.

03:50.931 --> 03:53.999
Signs are positive,
and the doctors...

03:54.001 --> 03:57.302
We are confident that
she's going to get better.

03:57.304 --> 03:59.972
INTERVIEWER: Well, I'm guessing
that the patch is no longer working

03:59.974 --> 04:02.374
<i>- at this stage in the disease.</i>
- CRAIG: <i> No.</i>

04:02.376 --> 04:04.276
<i>She's been put into
an induced coma</i>

04:04.278 --> 04:06.778
<i>in order to limit
her brain activity</i>

04:06.780 --> 04:08.714
<i>to try to stop the virus
from spreading.</i>

04:14.288 --> 04:15.721
(MAN SPEAKING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

04:16.790 --> 04:17.856
(INSIYA SPEAKING)

04:20.261 --> 04:21.493
(MAN SPEAKING)

04:34.575 --> 04:36.041
(MUMBLES INDISTINCTLY)

04:37.578 --> 04:39.011
- (GROWLS)
- (SCREAMS)

04:40.381 --> 04:41.713
(GRUNTING)

04:45.586 --> 04:46.785
(INSIYA GASPS)

04:50.424 --> 04:51.623
(GROANS)

04:52.026 --> 04:53.492
(PANTING)

05:29.096 --> 05:30.696
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

05:47.514 --> 05:50.582
MAN: She's holding steady, Craig.
We're on track.

05:54.355 --> 05:56.688
Her vitals are strong.
Scans are clear.

05:57.991 --> 06:00.826
When we cut back on the drugs,
we see the difference.

06:00.828 --> 06:02.761
She's fighting it, Craig.

06:14.608 --> 06:16.808
MAN: <i>We're still trying
to wrap this up,</i>

06:16.809 --> 06:19.009
<i>but doesn't look like they
want to budge from that number.</i>

06:19.012 --> 06:22.047
<i>They've got so much tied up
in that turbine deal.</i>

06:22.049 --> 06:25.384
<i>We're sending Jenson over to the
UAE office to meet with them again.</i>

06:26.587 --> 06:28.019
Okay, keep me in the loop.

06:29.923 --> 06:31.723
(REPORTER SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY
ON TV)

06:42.603 --> 06:44.703
When did you
start drinking local?

06:44.705 --> 06:46.805
- Since my guy jacked up the prices.
- (CHUCKLES)

06:47.875 --> 06:49.574
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

06:52.012 --> 06:53.545
(COUGHS)

06:53.547 --> 06:55.914
Holy shit! (GRUNTS)

06:57.084 --> 06:58.751
Hey, do you mind looking
at that?

06:58.752 --> 07:01.232
- I think the connection's got cacked out or something.
- Sure.

07:03.457 --> 07:04.856
What's this?

07:04.858 --> 07:06.792
Wind energy.

07:06.794 --> 07:09.094
It's the wave
of the future apparently.

07:16.036 --> 07:17.836
Saw you on TV today.

07:19.973 --> 07:21.506
Pretty good.

07:23.777 --> 07:27.012
You know, if you could ever fix a
problem by denying it ever existed,

07:27.014 --> 07:29.181
this place would be
a fucking utopia.

07:42.896 --> 07:44.729
INSIYA: <i> Craig.</i>

07:44.731 --> 07:46.031
(VOICE ECHOES)

07:46.033 --> 07:47.766
<i>What are you trying to say?</i>

07:50.904 --> 07:53.004
<i>You know I can't
leave this place.</i>

07:56.977 --> 07:59.177
<i>You know how much
my work means to me.</i>

08:02.683 --> 08:05.884
Maybe this place wouldn't
be such a hell hole

08:05.886 --> 08:09.221
if you stop treating it like it
was some sort of endurance test.

08:20.934 --> 08:24.102
This guy, Farhan...

08:24.104 --> 08:28.874
uh, she would borrow his bike to drive
around in the parking lot sometimes.

08:28.876 --> 08:32.977
So one day she decides she wants to
take it out in the city for a cruise.

08:32.980 --> 08:36.181
I said, "There's no way
Farhan's letting you do that."

08:36.183 --> 08:39.251
"There's no way he's
going to know," she says.

08:39.253 --> 08:42.988
Goes around the first corner
and bang, straight into a car.

08:42.990 --> 08:45.957
And not just any car.
It was a lab instructor.

08:46.793 --> 08:48.927
Luckily, though,
no one got hurt.

08:48.928 --> 08:51.062
But her father had to come in
and calm the whole situation down

08:51.064 --> 08:52.898
and get her out
of some deep shit.

09:06.113 --> 09:07.846
I feel like every day
I got to...

09:09.783 --> 09:12.050
find a way to keep
her alive in my mind.

09:17.324 --> 09:18.924
Seeing her...

09:21.128 --> 09:22.894
lying in that bed...

09:26.099 --> 09:27.799
a part of me...

09:28.869 --> 09:31.703
(SIGHS) ...wants to...

09:31.705 --> 09:34.339
forget this place in
my life ever existed.

09:46.720 --> 09:48.620
WOMAN: (ON RADIO)
<i>The cold reality, Vikas.</i>

09:48.622 --> 09:51.723
<i>These are slums with people
living on daily wages.</i>

09:52.859 --> 09:55.961
(DISTORTED)
<i>I've been to this places...</i>

09:59.032 --> 10:00.265
- (TIRES SCREECH)
- (GRUNTS)

10:36.903 --> 10:38.269
(SNARLING)

10:42.943 --> 10:44.175
(GUNSHOT FIRED)

10:49.650 --> 10:51.082
(SPEAKS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

11:21.181 --> 11:22.947
(MAN SPEAKS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

11:36.163 --> 11:37.696
(FLIES BUZZING)

11:48.041 --> 11:50.241
So you just got out of the car?

11:51.712 --> 11:53.078
Yeah.

11:53.080 --> 11:54.880
How close did he come
to taking your head off?

11:57.451 --> 11:59.951
Well, he got a piece.

11:59.953 --> 12:01.319
That's his blood on your shirt.

12:02.789 --> 12:04.829
You're very lucky, though.
The test came back clean.

12:25.479 --> 12:27.145
(SIZZLING)

12:30.417 --> 12:31.916
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

13:18.932 --> 13:20.298
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

13:31.011 --> 13:33.095
Hello.

13:33.096 --> 13:35.180
WOMAN: (ON PHONE) <i>Am I
speaking to Mr. Craig Evans?</i>

13:35.882 --> 13:37.282
Who is this?

13:38.185 --> 13:40.218
<i>My name is Amina.</i>

13:40.220 --> 13:42.187
<i>I'm the one who left
those papers.</i>

13:42.189 --> 13:44.422
Yeah. Are you sure
those are for me?

13:45.225 --> 13:46.591
<i>Yes, Mr. Evans.</i>

13:47.427 --> 13:50.361
Why? What is this about?

13:50.363 --> 13:52.430
<i>I need to see you
as soon as possible.</i>

13:54.100 --> 13:56.067
<i>It's about the MN-2.</i>

14:33.373 --> 14:34.639
(CAR LOCK BEEPS)

15:18.251 --> 15:21.452
I apologize you having to come
all this way, Mr. Evans.

15:24.624 --> 15:27.191
My husband's name
is Shehzad Ameen.

15:28.161 --> 15:30.295
He's a reporter for Saiyaara.

15:32.999 --> 15:36.034
Yes, I've seen him...
on television.

15:36.703 --> 15:39.570
Three days ago he disappeared.

15:42.542 --> 15:45.209
Shehzad thought he had found
something important.

15:46.046 --> 15:47.211
Proof.

15:48.515 --> 15:51.616
- Proof of what?
- I'm not sure.

15:51.618 --> 15:55.420
Something about the patch,
the disease.

15:55.422 --> 15:58.523
He's been warned
to keep his eyes closed.

15:59.559 --> 16:01.125
Let this pass.

16:03.163 --> 16:05.229
But there was no
talking sense into him.

16:10.303 --> 16:14.038
Mrs. Ameen, why did you
send me those papers?

16:14.741 --> 16:17.241
You have to help me.

16:17.243 --> 16:19.444
My husband's life is in danger.

16:20.680 --> 16:22.280
This story is tragic but...

16:22.282 --> 16:23.982
This is no story, this is real!

16:25.218 --> 16:27.552
This a matter for the police.

16:27.554 --> 16:30.488
You're talking about kidnapping
and who knows what else.

16:30.490 --> 16:34.325
You're American.
You can do anything you want.

16:34.327 --> 16:36.995
I saw you on TV, and I said,

16:36.997 --> 16:40.098
"This is the only man
who can help me."

16:40.100 --> 16:41.766
You can talk to someone
in your country.

16:41.768 --> 16:44.202
- Get to the bottom of all this...
- No!

16:46.740 --> 16:49.607
The police won't help me.

17:12.098 --> 17:13.377
(MAN SPEAKING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

17:24.277 --> 17:25.710
(MAN SPEAKING)

17:44.064 --> 17:45.596
(SHEHZAD SPEAKING)

17:46.599 --> 17:48.466
(MAN SPEAKING)

17:51.604 --> 17:53.204
INSIYA: Craig.

17:57.544 --> 17:59.077
Craig.

18:57.670 --> 18:59.203
(BONES CRACKING)

19:01.341 --> 19:02.473
(GASPS)

19:04.644 --> 19:06.410
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

19:31.304 --> 19:32.503
(DOOR OPENS)

19:34.941 --> 19:37.575
He would go there to work sometimes.
This is the key.

21:16.009 --> 21:17.275
MAN: Hello.

21:19.946 --> 21:21.512
Uh, hello.

21:21.514 --> 21:22.747
Craig.

21:22.749 --> 21:24.682
I'm a friend of Shehzad's,

21:24.684 --> 21:26.050
a friend of the family.

21:26.052 --> 21:28.552
I, uh... (CLEARS THROAT)
They gave me the key.

21:29.589 --> 21:31.555
MAN: I live across the hall.

21:31.557 --> 21:33.424
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

21:37.497 --> 21:39.997
Sometimes I would walk in
and it seemed like

21:39.999 --> 21:42.533
he had done nothing
but smoke all night.

21:44.437 --> 21:45.503
Other times...

21:46.639 --> 21:48.839
I'd hear voices
from behind the door.

21:50.576 --> 21:51.676
Loud voices.

21:52.679 --> 21:53.744
Arguments.

21:58.384 --> 22:00.451
CRAIG: That night
that he disappeared...

22:01.321 --> 22:03.421
He wouldn't sit for a minute.

22:03.423 --> 22:05.389
Kept walking around here.

22:05.391 --> 22:07.425
Back and forth, back and forth.

22:07.427 --> 22:09.994
Did he mention that he
was going to meet someone?

22:09.996 --> 22:11.062
Maybe a name.

22:12.365 --> 22:13.431
No.

22:14.334 --> 22:16.033
But he did use my cell phone.

22:17.036 --> 22:19.003
He said
he didn't want to use his.

22:20.373 --> 22:21.872
May I see it?

22:21.874 --> 22:22.940
(SPEAKS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

22:39.992 --> 22:42.026
(LINE RINGING)

22:51.137 --> 22:53.371
- MAN: (ON PHONE) Hello.
- My name is Craig Evans.

22:54.540 --> 22:55.906
I'm a friend of Shehzad Ameen.

22:56.542 --> 22:57.608
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

23:33.413 --> 23:35.613
(SPEAKING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

24:15.955 --> 24:17.455
Now, how is that possible?

24:42.482 --> 24:43.848
(WOMAN GROANS)

24:46.486 --> 24:47.985
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

25:07.974 --> 25:10.508
CRAIG: <i>I'm gonna wait
for the perfect moment.</i>

25:17.216 --> 25:18.165
I'm gonna look him in the eye...

25:18.166 --> 25:20.326
and I'm gonna tell him
I'm gonna marry his daughter.

25:29.662 --> 25:30.728
MAN: How's work?

25:32.965 --> 25:34.298
It's fine.

25:34.300 --> 25:35.566
Hmm.

25:38.104 --> 25:39.169
Garden's looking nice.

25:41.140 --> 25:42.606
Hmm, thank you.

25:48.748 --> 25:49.914
I wanna try to get her back.

25:50.783 --> 25:52.116
What?

25:52.118 --> 25:53.478
I wanna get her back
to the States.

25:55.555 --> 25:56.620
Why?

25:58.024 --> 25:59.664
I'll have her looked
at by another doctor.

26:00.059 --> 26:01.158
Do more tests.

26:02.995 --> 26:04.061
Get a second opinion.

26:04.864 --> 26:05.930
Third.

26:07.033 --> 26:08.799
Doctors here aren't white,

26:08.801 --> 26:10.701
but that doesn't mean
they're no good.

26:10.703 --> 26:13.270
Rias is our top man.

26:13.272 --> 26:16.106
There's no one more qualified
than him to take care of her.

26:16.108 --> 26:17.588
Maybe there's something
we're missing.

26:19.345 --> 26:21.612
It's not convenient for you
to be here

26:21.614 --> 26:23.748
with your work and travel.

26:23.749 --> 26:25.883
But I don't see what that has
to do with my daughter.

26:25.885 --> 26:27.618
What if we're getting locked
into something

26:27.620 --> 26:29.687
without knowing
all the possibilities first?

26:29.689 --> 26:30.955
What possibilities?

26:30.957 --> 26:32.990
You think I haven't explored
all of them?

26:32.992 --> 26:34.325
You think that I would
just leave her

26:34.327 --> 26:36.561
in some hospital hoping
for the best?

26:36.562 --> 26:38.796
If there is a chance,
if there is a fraction of a chance...

26:38.798 --> 26:42.066
No one can give her the care and
attention she's getting here.

26:44.870 --> 26:46.170
She's not going anywhere...

26:47.006 --> 26:48.372
in case I wasn't clear.

27:17.370 --> 27:18.769
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

27:24.310 --> 27:25.376
Hello.

27:25.378 --> 27:26.677
MAN: (ON PHONE) <i>Who is this?</i>

27:27.947 --> 27:29.147
I've been trying to reach you.

27:30.783 --> 27:31.949
<i>How do you know Shehzad?</i>

27:33.219 --> 27:34.785
Who am I speaking to?

27:34.787 --> 27:36.420
<i>Shehzad, how do you know him?</i>

27:36.422 --> 27:38.122
<i>Where did you get these papers?</i>

27:38.124 --> 27:41.091
I'm a friend.
His wife gave them to me.

27:42.094 --> 27:43.293
You know where Shehzad is?

27:44.063 --> 27:45.229
<i>No.</i>

27:45.231 --> 27:46.864
Did you give him these papers?

27:46.866 --> 27:48.799
<i>I, I, I can't talk to you
on this phone.</i>

27:50.169 --> 27:51.235
Then where?

28:38.451 --> 28:40.217
MAN: I was working at Ingenec
at that time.

28:47.026 --> 28:48.759
I can't remember
who recommended him.

28:49.729 --> 28:51.078
I remember

28:51.079 --> 28:52.719
somebody that knew me,
called me up and...

28:54.266 --> 28:55.799
wanted me to meet this guy

28:55.801 --> 28:57.901
who was doing the story
on pharmaceuticals...

28:57.903 --> 28:59.103
for some news channel.

29:01.140 --> 29:02.790
He really knew

29:02.791 --> 29:04.631
how to make somebody feel
like a piece of shit.

29:07.146 --> 29:08.479
He had a real gift for it.

29:10.049 --> 29:11.982
(SPEAKS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

29:13.819 --> 29:15.219
Farooq.

29:15.221 --> 29:16.954
Don't you see
what's going on here?

29:18.224 --> 29:19.289
Do the right thing.

29:23.229 --> 29:25.329
The night he disappeared...

29:25.331 --> 29:26.930
he talked to you, right?

29:26.932 --> 29:28.265
Yeah, he called.

29:38.110 --> 29:39.977
FAROOQ: He knew
they were on to him.

29:39.979 --> 29:42.780
He knew he was over,
he had nowhere to go.

29:42.782 --> 29:44.181
CRAIG: And do you know
what happened to him?

29:44.183 --> 29:45.249
FAROOQ: No.

29:46.819 --> 29:47.885
But I can guess.

29:56.462 --> 29:59.062
This is about the drug tests,

29:59.064 --> 30:00.931
the clinical trials.

30:00.933 --> 30:02.332
FAROOQ: That's all in
the early days.

30:02.334 --> 30:04.454
That's irrelevant.
That's just the tip of the iceberg.

30:05.971 --> 30:07.131
Shehzad had found out that...

30:09.408 --> 30:10.688
that they had found the cure.

30:15.347 --> 30:16.413
Please.

30:28.460 --> 30:29.526
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

30:29.528 --> 30:30.594
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

30:46.312 --> 30:47.377
Hmm.

30:48.314 --> 30:49.379
(SPEAKS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

31:16.942 --> 31:18.475
MAN: You're going to need a lot
more evidence

31:18.477 --> 31:21.078
for a story like this.

31:21.080 --> 31:22.980
Some time ago,
he came up with a story.

31:23.616 --> 31:25.349
A corrupt government official,

31:25.351 --> 31:26.617
very high ranking,

31:26.619 --> 31:28.552
accepting a bribe in some

31:28.554 --> 31:30.520
highway construction scandal.

31:30.522 --> 31:32.055
It was a spicy story.

31:32.057 --> 31:33.123
Made a big splash.

31:34.260 --> 31:35.325
Put him on the map.

31:38.264 --> 31:39.329
Except for one thing.

31:40.199 --> 31:41.265
He made it all up.

31:43.168 --> 31:44.501
You see, around here, everyone,

31:44.503 --> 31:46.970
from the ministers
to the tea boy think that they

31:46.972 --> 31:49.940
understand the root
of this country's problems.

31:49.942 --> 31:52.109
Shit doesn't just happen
around here.

31:52.111 --> 31:55.145
Everything is part of some
masterplan.

31:56.448 --> 31:58.048
And Shehzad...

31:58.050 --> 31:59.917
He just gives the viewers
what they want.

32:00.686 --> 32:02.085
There is no conspiracy.

32:03.155 --> 32:04.221
No cure.

32:06.125 --> 32:07.357
And this sort of talk is...

32:08.027 --> 32:09.092
dangerous.

32:18.304 --> 32:20.537
MARIAM: Mr. Evans, Mr. Evans.

32:25.144 --> 32:26.310
I'm Mariam.

32:26.312 --> 32:28.078
I work on Waqas's show.

33:24.603 --> 33:27.270
MARIAM: I'm the one who gave
Amina your contact information.

33:32.778 --> 33:34.077
Those rigged trials...

33:35.581 --> 33:37.381
that is what this is about,
right?

33:39.084 --> 33:40.684
Did you find anything,
anything more?

33:40.686 --> 33:42.352
You want Shehzad's story.

33:44.623 --> 33:46.189
I'm just trying to help.

33:46.191 --> 33:48.058
In exchange for whatever
I can find out.

33:49.094 --> 33:50.227
I saw Shehzad.

33:52.598 --> 33:55.165
<i>Sultan, the head guy
from Ingenec was there.</i>

33:55.167 --> 33:57.467
(REPORTER SPEAKS
IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

33:57.469 --> 33:58.769
SULTAN: Excuse me, excuse me.

33:58.771 --> 34:01.371
(SPEAKS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

34:02.508 --> 34:04.541
(SPEAKS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

34:08.746 --> 34:10.547
(SHEHZAD SPEAKS)

34:10.549 --> 34:12.081
(MAN SPEAKS)

34:18.424 --> 34:20.357
MARIAM:
I did catch this one name.

34:21.793 --> 34:23.060
Jarvis.

34:53.158 --> 34:55.192
(SPEAKING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

35:02.501 --> 35:04.668
(SHEHZAD SCREAMS)

35:08.807 --> 35:10.574
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

35:18.350 --> 35:19.883
REPORTER: (ON TV)
<i>Shehzad Ameen's body was found</i>

35:19.885 --> 35:21.618
<i>in the early hours
of the morning.</i>

35:21.620 --> 35:23.220
<i>Tests have confirmed the traces</i>

35:23.222 --> 35:24.754
<i>of the virus in Amin's blood.</i>

35:24.756 --> 35:26.823
<i>And the police have stated
there is little doubt</i>

35:26.825 --> 35:29.226
<i>that Amin was also a victim
of such an attack.</i>

35:30.229 --> 35:31.728
<i>The time of death
has been put at</i>

35:31.730 --> 35:33.864
<i>approximately,
1:00 a.m. last night.</i>

35:59.758 --> 36:01.791
(INAUDIBLE)

36:19.244 --> 36:20.510
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

37:03.822 --> 37:05.388
(SIGHS)

37:38.390 --> 37:40.023
(MAN SPEAKS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

